<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,284,563]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,606,284,311]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis (extracted from literature).</emphasis>
Female. Length 2.0 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[910,983,284,311]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Color.</emphasis>
Body light castaneous, metasoma dark castaneous. Head quadrate, vertex almost straight, corner rounded. Eye dark, rounded with six facets. Malar space short. Mesotibia strongly spinose. Metasoma elongate and lanceolate as long as head and mesosoma together.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,284,563]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,392,419]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[343,546,392,419]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[343,546,392,419]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Apenesia modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[802,955,392,418]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Sclerodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[802,955,392,418]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Sclerodermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Since we were not able to access the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,393,419]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">type</typeStatus>
for this study, the diagnosis here provided was obtained from the descriptions by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, F." box="[1091,1241,428,455]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="6 - 48" refId="ref51231" refString="Smith, F. (1864) Catalogue of hymenopterous insects collected by Mr. A. Wallace in the Islands of Mysol, Ceram, Waigiou, Bouru and Timor. Journal of the Proceeding of the Linnean Society, Zoology Suplement, 7, 6 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1863. tb 02085. x" type="journal article" year="1864">Smith (1864)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood, J. O." pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="ref51667" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1874) Thesaurus Entomologicus Oxoniensis. Clarendon Press, Oxford, 205 pp." type="book" year="1874">Westwood’s (1874)</bibRefCitation>
. Smith defined 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[405,529,464,491]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[405,529,464,491]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
especially using color details. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood, J. O." box="[1026,1227,464,491]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" refId="ref51667" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1874) Thesaurus Entomologicus Oxoniensis. Clarendon Press, Oxford, 205 pp." type="book" year="1874">Westwood (1874)</bibRefCitation>
, the mouthparts of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[151,275,500,527]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[151,275,500,527]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">A. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to 
<emphasis box="[437,597,501,527]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[437,593,501,527]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica">A. amazonica</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[654,702,501,527]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">type</typeStatus>
material is supposed to be deposited at OXUM.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
